🔹 Primitive vs Non-Primitive Data Types in C++
🔹 1. Primitive Data Types
👉 Definition

Primitive data types are basic built-in data types provided by C++

🔹 Examples
int
float
double
char
bool
🔹 Features

✔️ Predefined
✔️ Stores single value
✔️ Fast and simple

🔹 2. Non-Primitive Data Types
👉 Definition

Non-primitive data types are derived or user-defined types built using primitive types

🔹 Examples
Arrays → int arr[5]
Strings → string
Structures → struct
Classes → class
Unions → union
Pointers → int*
🔹 Features

✔️ Complex
✔️ Can store multiple values
✔️ User-defined / derived

🔥 Final Difference Table
Feature	Primitive	Non-Primitive
Type	Basic	Complex
Defined by	Language	User / Derived
Stores	Single value	Multiple / structured data
Example	int, float	array, class, struct